      "content": "fair enough. so if the \"aggregate benefits\" are mostly just numbers on a ledger but the actual people on the ground are the ones feeling the squeeze, does it even make sense for a government to push for more immigration from an economic standpoint? or is there a point where the \"macro\" gains stop being valid if they cause too much instability?",
